{title: Were You There?}
{subtitle: African American Passion spiritual, publ. 1899}
{key: Dm}
{time: 12/8}
{tempo: 56}
{comment: First spiritual ever published in a major denominational hymnal (Episcopal, 1940). Sung very slowly and prayerfully for Good Friday.}

{start_of_verse: 1}
[Dm]Were you there when they cru[Gm]cified my [Dm]Lord?
[Dm]Were you there when they cru[Gm]cified my [A7]Lord?
[Gm]Oh, [F]sometimes it causes [Dm]me to tremble, [A7]tremble, [Dm]tremble
[Dm]Were you there when they cru[A7]cified my [Dm]Lord?
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: 2}
